  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reduction of Economic and Human Loss and Displacement by Natural Disasters through Community-Based Resilience-Building and the Capacity-Building of the Government at All Levels in Papua New Guinea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to contribute to the reduction of economic and human loss and displacement by natural disasters through building community-based resilience and the capacity of government officials of all levels in Papua New Guinea. It aims to not only reduce and recover from losses from disasters by increasing national government&#x2019;s capacity but also to reinforce coordination and collaboration mechanisms among national and international humanitarian actors and involvement of faith-based groups and the private sector in all phases of an emergency. This approach fosters more effective utilization of existing resources, communication, and logistical networks to ensure timely outreach to affected remote communities.</narrative>
  </description>
